{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_83","type":"agent_message","text":"The docs point to a more specific limitation here: reflection metadata covers `Class.forName`, but non-built-in class loader loads are called out separately, and GraalVM 25 adds `-H:Preserve=...` specifically to keep those classes in the image for runtime loading. I’m checking whether this repo already solves similar fixtures with `Preserve` build args before I touch the test project."}}
